column7: Replace End Screw with Stop Plate on both sides of Rail to reflect the way the part is being purchased currently.  The end screw thread depths have been modified to be deeper to accommodate longer screws used for stage lockdown for shipping.  Field service issue was received (TI Automotive Poland MVQ2003559 installation problems). This has been an ongoing issue often discovered in outgoing inspection. Current fix is to supply a baggy with the vendor supplied hardware.

column7: Removed two End Screws (one on each end) and added Stop Plate and two  screws to secure the Stop Plate on both ends. Stop Plates and screws are supplied with the Rail.  Current rail end tapped holes have a tapped depth between 6 and 8mm. This has been changed to 12mm to accommodate shipping requirements.
